The paper deals with the controllability and observability of networked systems with linear time invariant dynamics, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of transmission zeros and connection matrices suggests a focus on networked systems and networked control (cs.NI). The application of the results to steady state estimation accuracy implies a connection to signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). The use of matrices and conditions for equivalence suggests a connection to linear algebra and matrix analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the use of distributed predictors and Kalman filters suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
